docs.abstract: President Trump’s acceptance of a disputed Saudi account of the death of Jamal Khashoggi suggests how he plans to ride out the most acute foreign policy crisis of his presidency.
docs.snippet: President Trump’s acceptance of a disputed Saudi account of the death of Jamal Khashoggi suggests how he plans to ride out the most acute foreign policy crisis of his presidency.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — His Democratic opponents do not believe it. His Republican allies don’t buy it. Even President Trump has ample reason, based on the intelligence reports he has seen, to doubt Saudi Arabia’s account of what happened to Jamal Khashoggi.

headline.main: Trump Wagers That Voters Will Shrug at a Saudi Storm
headline.print_headline: Trump Wagers That Voters Won’t Remember This Crisis Either

docs.abstract: The location of the attack was a small strip of desert frequently used by a military unit, prompting Taliban militants to bury explosives nearby.
docs.snippet: The location of the attack was a small strip of desert frequently used by a military unit, prompting Taliban militants to bury explosives nearby.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The death of an Army soldier after a blast in southern Afghanistan this month was the result of a series of oversights by a military unit that frequently used a small strip of desert as a patrol route and observation post, prompting Taliban militants to bury explosives nearby, military officials familiar with the matter said.

headline.main: Series of Lapses Led to Army Soldier’s Death in Afghanistan
headline.print_headline: Series of Oversights Led  To U.S. Soldier’s Death

docs.abstract: In a year when Democrats are on offense, Pete Stauber of Minnesota has a chance to do something no other Republican might do next month: win a Democratic House seat.
docs.snippet: In a year when Democrats are on offense, Pete Stauber of Minnesota has a chance to do something no other Republican might do next month: win a Democratic House seat.
docs.lead_paragraph: GRAND RAPIDS, Minn. — For 70 of the past 72 years, a Democrat has represented this rural corner of northern Minnesota in Congress. But when loggers, foresters and truckers convened on the county fairgrounds here for the annual timber industry expo last month, the star of the “celebrity log-loading” contest was a Republican.

headline.main: Meet the Republicans’ Best Hope for Flipping a House Seat
headline.print_headline: Courting Other Side  And Giving the G.O.P.   A Chance to Flip a Seat

docs.abstract: It appears to be the first time that the campaign of a sitting president facing re-election has opted to market its list of voter contacts.
docs.snippet: It appears to be the first time that the campaign of a sitting president facing re-election has opted to market its list of voter contacts.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Early in his presidential campaign, Donald J. Trump dismissed political data as an “overrated” tool. But after he won the Republican nomination, his team began building a database that offers a pipeline into the heart of the party’s base, a comprehensive list including the email addresses and cellphone numbers of as many as 20 million supporters.

headline.main: Now for Rent: Email Addresses and Phone Numbers for Millions of Trump Supporters
headline.print_headline: Now for Rent: Emails and Phone Numbers for Millions of Trump Supporters

docs.abstract: So far, economists see only faint effects of the new tax law in housing prices. The predicted carnage hasn’t materialized.
docs.snippet: So far, economists see only faint effects of the new tax law in housing prices. The predicted carnage hasn’t materialized.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It wasn’t supposed to take long for the Trump tax cuts to hobble housing prices, particularly in the high-tax, high-cost metro areas where the new law was poised to rip federal incentives to buy new homes.

headline.main: The Trump Tax Cuts Were Supposed to Depress Housing Prices. They Haven’t.
headline.print_headline: Tax Cuts Were Going to Tank Housing Prices. They Didn’t.

docs.abstract: The South Carolina senator urged the administration to exclude imports used by companies from his state from a list of products subject to tariffs.
docs.snippet: The South Carolina senator urged the administration to exclude imports used by companies from his state from a list of products subject to tariffs.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Lindsey Graham of South Carolina has been one of the biggest proponents of President Trump’s crackdown on China, welcoming tariffs on Chinese imports while conceding that they will raise costs for American businesses and consumers.

headline.main: Lindsey Graham Welcomed Trump’s China Tariffs, Then Helped Companies Avoid Them
headline.print_headline: Pro Tariffs, but Protecting Friends From Pain

docs.abstract: As the nation remembers the former president, we assess some popular anecdotes about him, including his reaction to a grocery store scanner and whether Ross Perot cost him a second term.
docs.snippet: As the nation remembers the former president, we assess some popular anecdotes about him, including his reaction to a grocery store scanner and whether Ross Perot cost him a second term.
docs.lead_paragraph: After his defeat in the 1992 election, former President George Bush concluded that he lost his bid for a second term because he “just wasn’t a good enough communicator” and blamed the news media for the perception that he was out of touch with the average American. Certain claims are again abounding as the country prepares to bury Mr. Bush after his death on Friday. Here’s a look at some of them.

headline.main: George Bush’s Legacy: Revisiting Past Claims

docs.abstract: President Trump said Ms. Nauert “has done a great job” at the State Department. But she would bring less experience in government or international affairs to her new job than almost anyone who has had it.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump confirmed on Friday that he would nominate Heather Nauert, a former “Fox & Friends” host who has served as the State Department spokeswoman since last year, to replace Nikki R. Haley as ambassador to the United Nations and help promote an “America First” foreign policy that has at times rankled some of the country’s leading allies.

headline.main: Heather Nauert’s Pick as U.N. Envoy Hints at Reshaping of the Role
headline.print_headline: Résumé Heavy on TV Journalism, Light on Politics, May See New Title: U.N. Envoy

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Paul Manafort, President Trump’s former campaign chairman, lied to federal investigators about his contacts with Trump administration officials and his interactions with a Russian linked to Moscow’s intelligence services, the special counsel’s office said on Friday.

docs.snippet: But the justices seemed reluctant to overrule precedents that sometimes allow defendants to be prosecuted twice for the same crimes.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In an extended argument on Thursday that touched on history, the role of precedent and fundamental questions of constitutional interpretation, the Supreme Court considered whether it should overrule a series of decisions that sometimes allowed criminal defendants to be prosecuted twice for the same crimes.

headline.print_headline: A Case With Implications  For Some Trump Friends
